Instance variable may correspond to Java Beans properties --> class attribute.


Entity Class must:

1. have No-arg constructor public or protected
2. be Top level class
3. implement Serializable interface, **IF** its instance is passed by value as a detached object
4. access an instance variable directly by the instance itself

Entity class must not:

1. be an Enum or Interface 
2. be final 
3. have methods or persistent instance variable as final
4. allow client classes to by their client classes (Client classes must access entity class state through accessor methods)

Entity supports Inheritance, polymorphic association and polymorphic queries

Entity classes may:

1. be abstract or concrete classes
2. extend a non-entity classes
3. extend an entity classes
4. be extend by a non-entity class 




